    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Harvey</persName> to <persName type="to">Commander
                        Preble</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 22, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Having communicated with his Majesty’s government
                    upon the matter of information contained in your letters of the 10th and 13th
                    instant, addressed to this legation, there is no reason, within my knowledge,
                    why the St. Louis should be detained longer in port.</p>
                <p>On the contrary, it is desirable that she should proceed immediately to the
                    Azores for the protection of our exposed commerce and interests, guided by the
                    information which you already possess, or which you may hereafter receive. The
                    island of Terceira requires particular vigilance.</p>
                <p>It is also desirable that the island of Teneriffe should be included in your
                    proposed cruise. These suggestions will be made known to the Navy Department at
                    Washington.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES E. HARVEY.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Commander <hi rend="smallcaps">G. H. Preble</hi>, <hi rend="italic">United
                            States Steamer St. Louis.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
